EB Bootstrap Methods - CV Once

By Logan Harris, Advised by Patrick Breheny Last updated 2023-09-28 14:45

source("./R/bayes_functions.R")

library(TeachingDemos)
my_seed <- char2seed("Logan M. Harris")

One Covariate

Beta = 0

Single Interval

Original

set.seed(my_seed)
tmp <- eb_boot(beta = 0, p = 1, b = 0, n = 30, nboot = 100, type = "original", time = TRUE)
# Generate data: 0.001 sec elapsed
# Cross Validation: 0.01 sec elapsed
# Bootstrapping: 0.523 sec elapsed
# Overall: 0.535 sec elapsed
int_b0_O <- c(mean(tmp$lower), mean(tmp$upper))

Univariate

set.seed(my_seed)
tmp <- eb_boot(beta = 0, p = 1, b = 0, n = 30, nboot = 100, type = "univariate", time = TRUE)
# Generate data: 0.001 sec elapsed
# Cross Validation: 0.008 sec elapsed
# Bootstrapping: 0.06 sec elapsed
# Overall: 0.069 sec elapsed
int_b0_U <- c(mean(tmp$lower), mean(tmp$upper))

Coverage

Original

set.seed(my_seed)
res <- eb_boot_sim(beta = 0, p = 1, b = 0, n = 30, nboot = 100, nsim = 100, type = "original")
cov_b0_O <- mean(res$overall_cov)

Univariate

set.seed(my_seed)
res <- eb_boot_sim(beta = 0, p = 1, b = 0, n = 30, nboot = 100, nsim = 100, type = "univariate")
cov_b0_U <- mean(res$overall_cov)

Comparison

tbl <- data.frame("Original" = c(int_b0_O, cov_b0_O), "Univariate" = c(int_b0_U, cov_b0_U))
rownames(tbl) <- c("Lower (Single)", "Upper (Single)", "Coverage (100 Simulations)")
tbl %>% kbl() %>% kable_material(c("striped", "hover"))
Original Univariate
Lower (Single) -0.6897289 -0.6897276
Upper (Single) -0.1468659 -0.1468678
Coverage (100 Simulations) 0.8943333 0.8943333

Coverage

Original

set.seed(my_seed)
res <- eb_boot_sim(beta = c(2, 1, 0.5, -2, -1, -0.5), type = "original")
Overall Coverage (per bootstrap)
mean(res$overall_cov)
# [1] 0.8943333
hist(res$overall_cov, xlab = "Coverage", main ="")

Individual Coverage (per covariate)
tmp <- data.frame(coverage = apply(res$indiv_cov, 2, mean) , beta = res$truth)
plot(abs(tmp$beta), tmp$coverage, xlab = "True Beta Value", ylab = "Coverage")

Univariate

Real Data

Rhee2006

Pre-process data

  • Remove constant and perfectly colinear columns
dat <- readData(Rhee2006)
dup <- duplicated(t(dat$X))
const <- apply(dat$X, 2, function(x) length(unique(x)) == 1)
dat$X <- dat$X[,!dup & !const]

Perform Bootstrap / plot

set.seed(my_seed)
rhee <- eb_boot(dat = dat, type = "univariate", nboot = 200, time = TRUE)
# Cross Validation: 1.821 sec elapsed
# Bootstrapping: 13.821 sec elapsed
# Overall: 15.642 sec elapsed
plot_boot(rhee, n = 60)
# [1] "179 total variables with NA entries, summary: "
#    Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max. 
#    1.00    9.00   56.00   43.21   73.00   87.00

Number intervals not containing 0:

lowers <- apply(rhee[["lower"]], 2, mean, na.rm = TRUE)
uppers <- apply(rhee[["upper"]], 2, mean, na.rm = TRUE)
sum(sign(lowers) * sign(uppers) == 1)
# [1] 24
